
msgid "Tarantool 2.10.3"
msgstr ""

msgid "Released on 2022-09-30."
msgstr ""

msgid "Release: :tarantool-release:`2.10.3`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Tag: ``2.10.3``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"2.10.3 is the fourth :doc:`stable </release/policy/>` version of the 2.10 "
"release series. It introduces 2 improvements and resolves 19 bugs since "
"2.10.2."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The “stable” label means that we have all planned features implemented and "
"we see no high-impact issues. However, if you encounter an issue, feel free "
"to `report it <https://github.com/tarantool/tarantool/issues>`__ on GitHub."
msgstr ""

msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tarantool 2.x is backward compatible with Tarantool 1.10.x in the binary "
"data layout, client-server protocol, and replication protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Please :doc:`upgrade </book/admin/upgrades>` using the "
"``box.schema.upgrade()`` procedure to unlock all the new features of the 2.x"
" series."
msgstr ""

msgid "Functionality added or changed"
msgstr ""

msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

msgid "RedOS 7.3 is now supported."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Added the ``-DENABLE_HARDENING=ON/OFF`` CMake option that enables hardening "
"against memory corruption attacks (:tarantool-issue:`7536`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Bugs fixed"
msgstr ""

msgid "Core"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug introduced in Tarantool 2.10.2: log messages could be written to"
" data files thus causing data corruption. The issue was fixed by reverting "
"the fix for :tarantool-issue:`4450`."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Switched from MT-Unsafe ``strerror()`` to MT-Safe ``strerror_r()``. The "
"usage of the unsafe function could result in corrupted error messages."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a single JSON update couldn’t insert and update a field of "
"a map or an array in two sequential calls. It would either crash or return "
"an error (:tarantool-issue:`7705`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Memtx"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed incorrect handling of transaction conflicts in full scans by HASH "
"indexes (:tarantool-issue:`7493`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed ``use after free`` that could occur in the transaction manager in "
"certain states (:tarantool-issue:`7449`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed possible phantom reads with ``get`` on TREE indexes containing "
"nullable parts (:tarantool-issue:`7685`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an inconsistency in ``index:random`` in the context of transaction "
"management (:tarantool-issue:`7670`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed unserializable reads tracked incorrectly after transaction rollbacks "
"(:tarantool-issue:`7343`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Replication"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a fiber committing a synchronous transaction could hang if "
"the instance got a term bump during that or its synchro-queue was fenced in "
"any other way (:tarantool-issue:`7253`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed master occasionally deleting xlogs needed by replicas even without a "
"restart (:tarantool-issue:`7584`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Raft"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when ``box.ctl.promote()`` could hang and bump thousands of "
"terms in a row if called on more than one node at the same time (part of "
":tarantool-issue:`7253`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a node with ``election_mode='voter'`` could hang in "
"``box.ctl.promote()`` or become a leader (part of :tarantool-issue:`7253`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a replicaset could be split into parts if a node voted for "
"another instance while having local WAL writes unfinished (part of "
":tarantool-issue:`7253`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Lua"
msgstr ""

msgid "Merger"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed ``use after free`` that could occur during iteration over "
"``merge_source:pairs()`` or ``merger:pairs()`` (:tarantool-issue:`7657`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Popen"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a race condition in ``<popen handle>:signal()`` on Mac OS 12 and newer"
" (:tarantool-issue:`7658`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Box"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when ``fiber.yield()`` might break the execution of a shutdown "
"trigger (:tarantool-issue:`7434`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a possible high CPU usage caused by shutdown triggers (:tarantool-"
"issue:`6801`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Synchro"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed assertions in debug builds and undefined behaviour in release builds "
"when simultaneous elections started or another instance was promoted while "
"an instance was acquiring or releasing the synchro queue (:tarantool-"
"issue:`7086`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Uri"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in the URI parser: tarantoolctl could not connect when the host "
"name was skipped (:tarantool-issue:`7479`)."
msgstr ""
